    <headNote resp="MSPP">Speech was given on December 4th, 1934. For a summary see "Mrs. Sanger
        Speaker at Guest Meet," Casa Grande Dispatch, 12/07/1934, p.1. Margaret Sanger addressed 200
        women at the Women's Club in Casa Grande, Arizona. The program included poems, music and was
        followed by a social at which Sanger was presented with Mrs. Hager's "famous rattlesnake
        string of beads." No final version of the speech was found, just notes. <index
            level1="birth control" level2="civilization and"/>
